org.osgi.service.remoteservices
Interface EndpointDescription

public interface EndpointDescription

This interface describes the details of a communications endpoint. The use of this interface has the following purposes:

  1. When a distribution provider exports a service it creates a communications endpoint. The details of this endpoint can then be announced through a Endpoint Description
  2. A distribution provider can use a Endpoint Description to import a service.
  3. An Endpoint Description can be created for a non-OSGi service endpoint, for example a Google webservice
The Endpoint Description is easy to transfer between different systems. It can therefore be used in discovery or remote control schemes. EndpointDescription objects are immutable. ### are they serializable?? ### they must implement equals + hashCode

Field Detail

ENDPOINT_INTERFACE_VERSION_PREFIX

static final java.lang.String ENDPOINT_INTERFACE_VERSION_PREFIX
The prefix for the version of an interface. The actual property should have a value of ENDPOINT_INTERFACE_VERSION_PREFIX + FQN, where the FQN is the name fully qualified name of the interface. The value of the property must be a properly formatted OSGi version string. For example: 
        endpoint.interface.version.com.acme.foo.Foo = 3.0.0.v242112

getServiceUUID

java.lang.String getServiceUUID()
Returns the universally unique id for the service represented by this endpoint. Each service in the OSGi service registry has a universally unique id. The UUID can be used to detect that two Endpoint Descriptions really refer to the same registered service instance in some remote framework. This UUID can be used to filter out duplicate ways of communicating with the same service.

Returns:
Unique id of service represented by this endpoint, or null if it hasn't been provided.

getConfigurationType

java.lang.String getConfigurationType()
Returns the configuration types. A distribution provider exports a service with an endpoint. This endpoint uses some kind of communications protocol with a set of configuration parameters. There are many different types but each endpoint is configured by only one configuration type.

Returns:
The configuration type used for the associated endpoint.

getProperties

java.util.Map getProperties()
Returns all service endpoint properties.

Returns:
all properties of the service as a Map (<String, Object>). The map is never null or empty but contains at least mandatory ServicePublication properties. Since ServiceEndpointDescription objects are immutable, the returned map is also not going to be updated at a later point of time.

isLocal

boolean isLocal()
Answers if the described endpoint is local to this framework. This is defined as having the ENDPOINT_LOCAL property set to any value.

Returns:
true if this an endpoint originating on this framework is described, false otherwise.
